textBeforeTable: Fedora 17 Currently supported EC2 images Direct questions or comments to the Cloud SIG email list. Full documentation for interacting with EC2 is available from Amazon Web Services. The default username for the images is ec2-user. Fedora's EC2 images follow the standard EC2 login conventions, meaning that root login is disabled, but sudo access is granted. Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) 1.2 Custom image creation 1.1.2 Fedora 16 1.1.1 Fedora 17 1.1 Currently supported EC2 images 1 Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) Contents In addition to DVDs and Live CDs, the Fedora Project makes its distribution available on cloud computing architectures. These Fedora images provide an excellent (and extensible) foundation for your server or appliance. [edit]‪中文(中国大陆)‬ (zh-cn)English (en)In other languages: Revision as of 11:30, 27 November 2012
